## 1. Define your providers

### Selected brand provider

```dart
// brand_model.dart
class Brand {
  final String id;
  final String name;
  const Brand({required this.id, required this.name});
}
```

```dart
// providers.dart
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';
import 'brand_model.dart';

final selectedBrandProvider = StateProvider<Brand?>((ref) => null);
```

### Dashboard data provider that depends on selected brand

```dart
// providers.dart (continued)

// Simulated repository
class DashboardRepository {
  Future<String> fetchDashboardForBrand(String brandId) async {
    await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 500));
    return 'Dashboard data for brand: $brandId';
  }
}

final dashboardRepositoryProvider = Provider((ref) => DashboardRepository());

// This provider will automatically re-run when selectedBrand changes
final dashboardDataProvider = FutureProvider<String>((ref) async {
  final repo = ref.watch(dashboardRepositoryProvider);
  final brand = ref.watch(selectedBrandProvider);

  if (brand == null) {
    return 'No brand selected';
  }

  return repo.fetchDashboardForBrand(brand.id);
});
```

> Key idea: `dashboardDataProvider` **watches** `selectedBrandProvider`. When the brand changes, the dashboard data is fetched again.

