## 2. Drawer with brand list (using Riverpod)

```dart
class BrandDrawer extends ConsumerWidget {
  final List<Brand> brands;

  const BrandDrawer({super.key, required this.brands});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final selectedBrand = ref.watch(selectedBrandProvider);

    return Drawer(
      child: ListView(
        children: [
          const DrawerHeader(child: Text('Brands')),
          for (final brand in brands)
            ListTile(
              title: Text(brand.name),
              trailing: selectedBrand?.id == brand.id
                  ? const Icon(Icons.check)
                  : null,
              onTap: () {
                // ✅ update selected brand in Riverpod
                ref.read(selectedBrandProvider.notifier).state = brand;

                // close drawer
                Navigator.of(context).pop();

                // optional: navigate with go_router if needed
                // context.go('/dashboard');
              },
            ),
        ],
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

When the user taps a brand:

1. `selectedBrandProvider` is updated
2. Any widget watching `dashboardDataProvider` will automatically reload

