## 2) Network provider (StreamProvider)

Create a file `core/services/network.s.dart` (or wherever you keep services):

```dart
// core/services/network.s.dart
import 'dart:async';
import 'dart:io';
import 'package:connectivity_plus/connectivity_plus.dart';
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';

final networkStatusStreamProvider = StreamProvider<bool>((ref) {
  final connectivity = Connectivity();
  // Start with a single check then follow connectivity changes
  final controller = StreamController<bool>();

  Future<void> checkNow() async {
    try {
      final connResult = await connectivity.checkConnectivity();
      if (connResult == ConnectivityResult.none) {
        controller.add(false);
        return;
      }
      // Do a real connectivity check: try DNS lookup
      final result = await InternetAddress.lookup('example.com').timeout(const Duration(seconds: 4));
      controller.add(result.isNotEmpty && result[0].rawAddress.isNotEmpty);
    } catch (_) {
      controller.add(false);
    }
  }

  // initial check
  checkNow();

  final sub = connectivity.onConnectivityChanged.listen((_) async {
    await checkNow();
  });

  ref.onDispose(() {
    sub.cancel();
    controller.close();
  });

  return controller.stream.distinct();
});
```

Notes:
- The stream emits `true`/`false`. `distinct()` prevents duplicate consecutive values.
- `InternetAddress.lookup('example.com')` helps ensure actual internet (not just Wi-Fi connected).

