## Extra tips / gotchas
- `ref.listen` only triggers when the provider's value changes identity. For complex state objects, return immutable instances so changes fire listeners.
- We use `maybeWhen(data:..., orElse:...)` in redirect to avoid aggressively sending users to the offline page before the provider has determined status.
- I used `Navigator.pushReplacementNamed` in `NetworkLoosePage` for compatibility — if you prefer `context.go(...)` from `go_router`, replace it.
- If you prefer not to mutate provider state inside `redirect`, you can instead set `lastRouteBeforeOfflineProvider` from a `ref.listen` callback inside `RouterNotifier`. Doing it inside `redirect` is simple and works, but if you want to be purely side-effect-free in `redirect`, move that logic into the notifier.

