## Correct Riverpod Auth Notifier

Create a **ChangeNotifierProvider**:

```dart
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';
import 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';

class AuthCoreNotifier extends ChangeNotifier {
  bool _loggedIn = false;

  bool get isLoggedIn => _loggedIn;

  void setLoggedIn(bool value) {
    _loggedIn = value;
    notifyListeners();
  }
}

/// 👇 Riverpod provider
final authCoreProvider = ChangeNotifierProvider<AuthCoreNotifier>((ref) {
  return AuthCoreNotifier();
});
```

---

## Using it in widgets

### Read once (no UI update)
```dart
final auth = ref.read(authCoreProvider);
auth.setLoggedIn(true);
```

### Watch for changes (auto rebuild UI)
```dart
final auth = ref.watch(authCoreProvider);
bool loggedIn = auth.isLoggedIn;
```

---

## Using it inside GoRouter provider

```dart
final goRouterProvider = Provider<GoRouter>((ref) {
  final auth = ref.read(authCoreProvider);
  return AppRouter.createRouter(auth);
});
```

