## 2. Model for dynamic sections

```dart
// lib/models/dashboard_config.dart

class DashboardSection {
  final String type; // e.g. "banner", "nearby_outlet", ...
  final String title;
  final Map<String, dynamic> props;

  DashboardSection({
    required this.type,
    required this.title,
    required this.props,
  });

  factory DashboardSection.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) {
    return DashboardSection(
      type: json['type'] as String,
      title: json['title'] as String? ?? json['type'] as String,
      props: (json['props'] as Map<String, dynamic>? ?? {}),
    );
  }
}

class DashboardConfig {
  final String brandId;
  final List<DashboardSection> sections;

  DashboardConfig({
    required this.brandId,
    required this.sections,
  });

  factory DashboardConfig.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) {
    final List<dynamic> rawSections = json['sections'] as List<dynamic>? ?? [];
    return DashboardConfig(
      brandId: json['brandId'] as String,
      sections: rawSections
          .map((e) => DashboardSection.fromJson(e as Map<String, dynamic>))
          .toList(),
    );
  }
}
```

Your `dashboardsProvider` stays almost the same (just uses new model):

```dart
// lib/providers.dart (snippet for dashboardsProvider)
final dashboardsProvider = FutureProvider<List<DashboardConfig>>((ref) async {
  final jsonStr = await rootBundle.loadString('assets/dashboards.json');
  final List<dynamic> data = json.decode(jsonStr);
  return data
      .map((e) => DashboardConfig.fromJson(e as Map<String, dynamic>))
      .toList();
});
```

Other providers (`brandsProvider`, `selectedBrandProvider`, etc.) can remain as before, except where you previously used `widgets: List<String>` you now use `sections: List<DashboardSection>`.

