```

### `features/dashboard/common/base_dashboard_page.dart`

Inside this page, you decide which brand dashboard to show:

```dart
class BaseDashboardPage extends ConsumerWidget {
  const BaseDashboardPage({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final brand = ref.watch(currentBrandProvider);

    Widget content;
    switch (brand.id) {
      case 'brand_a':
        content = const BrandADashboardPage();
        break;
      case 'brand_b':
        content = const BrandBDashboardPage();
        break;
      case 'brand_c':
        content = const BrandCDashboardPage();
        break;
      case 'brand_d':
        content = const BrandDDashboardPage();
        break;
      case 'brand_e':
        content = const BrandEDashboardPage();
        break;
      default:
        content = const BrandADashboardPage();
    }

    return content;
  }
}
```

Each `BrandXDashboardPage` can also watch `currentBrandThemeProvider` for colors, but you already know which brand it is.

